Gecarcinus nobilii sp. n. is currently known to occur from Punta Galera and St. Elena (Ecuador). It is also documented in photographs taken at Gorgona Island (Colombia) (Fig. 4 A-C ), Chucheros Beach (Buenaventura, Colombia) (Fig. 4D), Canangucho Forest Reserve ( Nuqui , Choco , Colombia) (Fig. 4E), Ayampe ( Manabi , Ecuador) (Fig. 4F), and Isla de la Plata (Ecuador). Individuals of Gecarcinus previously reported from Peru (
Tuerkay 1970
) may also refer to Gecarcinus nobilii sp. n.

